Now we need to prove that every element of &quot;G&quot; is in &quot;H&quot;. Let formula_39 be an element of &quot;G&quot;. Since &quot;H&quot; is a closed subspace of &quot;G&quot;, we can write formula_108 where formula_109 and formula_110. Now if formula_111 then, since &quot;K&quot; is a reproducing kernel of &quot;G&quot; and &quot;H&quot;:

