This shows that formula_115 in &quot;G&quot; and concludes the proof.

==Integral operators and Mercer&#x27;s theorem==
We may characterize a symmetric positive definite kernel formula_65 via the integral operator using Mercer&#x27;s theorem and obtain an additional view of the RKHS. Let formula_2 be a compact space equipped with a strictly positive finite Borel measure formula_69 and formula_119 a continuous, symmetric, and positive definite function. Define the integral operator formula_120 as

:formula_121

where formula_122 is the space of square integrable functions with respect to formula_123.

Mercer&#x27;s theorem states that the spectral decomposition of the integral operator formula_124 of formula_65 yields a series representation of formula_65 in terms of the eigenvalues and eigenfunctions of formula_127. This then implies that formula_65 is a reproducing kernel so that the corresponding RKHS can be defined in terms of these eigenvalues and eigenfunctions. We provide the details below.

